{"id":810,"date":"2021-08-18T16:02:50","date_gmt":"2021-08-18T10:32:50","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/?p=810"},"modified":"2022-03-11T23:47:22","modified_gmt":"2022-03-12T05:17:22","slug":"heaviest-cars-in-the-world-ranked","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/heaviest-cars-in-the-world-ranked\/","title":{"rendered":"Heaviest Cars In The World &#8211; Ranked"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Being heavy means being slow, and inefficient, and cumbersome, and if stuck in a puddle &#8211; Impossible to get out of. That&#x2019;s of course, talking about cars. But being heavy can also sometimes mean a symbol of luxury.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Since the very begging, automakers have been trying and vying to shave off extra bits of weight from their cars to help improve their performance, practicality, and appeal. The weight of a car directly affects mileage, maneuvering, power, and all sorts of performance aspects. However, even then, there have been certain carmakers for whom being practical or efficient wasn&#x2019;t necessarily a priority and in an act of self-indulgence, made some of the heaviest, most inefficient but not always impractical vehicles around the world.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#x2019;s look at some of the heaviest four wheels on the planet in today&#x2019;s fat-shaming and unwoke feature of the heaviest cars in the world.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_50 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-transparent ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-toggle\"><\/span><\/div>\n<nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/heaviest-cars-in-the-world-ranked\/#Rolls_Royce_Phantom_%E2%80%93_2745kg\" title=\"Rolls Royce Phantom &#8211; 2745kg\">Rolls Royce Phantom &#8211; 2745kg<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/heaviest-cars-in-the-world-ranked\/#Bentley_Continental_Flying_Spur_%E2%80%93_2450_kg\" title=\"Bentley Continental Flying Spur &#8211; 2450 kg\">Bentley Continental Flying Spur &#8211; 2450 kg<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/heaviest-cars-in-the-world-ranked\/#Volkswagen_Touareg_W12_%E2%80%93_2524_kg\" title=\"Volkswagen Touareg W12 &#8211; 2524 kg\">Volkswagen Touareg W12 &#8211; 2524 kg<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/heaviest-cars-in-the-world-ranked\/#Buick_Estate_%E2%80%93_2351_kg\" title=\"Buick Estate &#8211; 2351 kg\">Buick Estate &#8211; 2351 kg<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/heaviest-cars-in-the-world-ranked\/#Audi_Q7_V12_%E2%80%93_2600_kg\" title=\"Audi Q7 V12 &#8211; 2600 kg\">Audi Q7 V12 &#8211; 2600 kg<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/heaviest-cars-in-the-world-ranked\/#Audi_E-Tron_SUV_%E2%80%93_2695_kg\" title=\"Audi E-Tron SUV &#8211; 2695 kg\">Audi E-Tron SUV &#8211; 2695 kg<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/heaviest-cars-in-the-world-ranked\/#Tesla_Cybertruck_%E2%80%93_3000_kg\" title=\"Tesla Cybertruck &#8211; 3000 kg&nbsp;\">Tesla Cybertruck &#8211; 3000 kg&nbsp;<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/heaviest-cars-in-the-world-ranked\/#Cadillac_Escalade_%E2%80%93_3447_kg\" title=\"Cadillac Escalade &#8211; 3447 kg\">Cadillac Escalade &#8211; 3447 kg<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/heaviest-cars-in-the-world-ranked\/#GMC_Hummer_EV_%E2%80%93_4103_kg\" title=\"GMC Hummer EV &#8211; 4,103 kg\">GMC Hummer EV &#8211; 4,103 kg<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-10\" href=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/heaviest-cars-in-the-world-ranked\/#Mercedes-Benz_770_K_Cabriolet_Armored_4800_kg\" title=\"Mercedes-Benz 770 K Cabriolet Armored 4800 kg\">Mercedes-Benz 770 K Cabriolet Armored 4800 kg<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Rolls_Royce_Phantom_%E2%80%93_2745kg\"><\/span>Rolls Royce Phantom &#8211; 2745kg<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rolls-royce-phantom-2017-465270-compressed.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-816\" width=\"384\" height=\"256\" srcset=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rolls-royce-phantom-2017-465270-compressed.jpg 768w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rolls-royce-phantom-2017-465270-compressed-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rolls-royce-phantom-2017-465270-compressed-24x16.jpg 24w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rolls-royce-phantom-2017-465270-compressed-36x24.jpg 36w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rolls-royce-phantom-2017-465270-compressed-48x32.jpg 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 384px) 100vw, 384px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#x2019;s start the list with the most obvious. We all know the kind of cars Rolls Royce makes. They are not a concern in terms of mileage, maneuvering, or getting stuck in a puddle, in fact, I think, they&#x2019;re probably not even meant to be driven by the owner. You would most definitely have a chauffeur to drive you around if you own a phantom. This is probably the reason why you wouldn&#x2019;t mind the fact that it&#x2019;s one of the most uneconomical cars out there. The opulent Rolls Royce phantom weighs more than 2 and a half-ton and stretches 239 inches in length.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Bentley_Continental_Flying_Spur_%E2%80%93_2450_kg\"><\/span>Bentley Continental Flying Spur &#8211; 2450 kg<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rp_-_flying_spur_v8-49-compressed-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-815\" width=\"512\" height=\"288\" srcset=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rp_-_flying_spur_v8-49-compressed-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rp_-_flying_spur_v8-49-compressed-300x169.jpg 300w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rp_-_flying_spur_v8-49-compressed-768x432.jpg 768w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rp_-_flying_spur_v8-49-compressed-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rp_-_flying_spur_v8-49-compressed-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rp_-_flying_spur_v8-49-compressed-850x478.jpg 850w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rp_-_flying_spur_v8-49-compressed-24x14.jpg 24w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rp_-_flying_spur_v8-49-compressed-36x20.jpg 36w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/rp_-_flying_spur_v8-49-compressed-48x27.jpg 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Being a higher than high-end luxury saloon, it is normal for the flying spur to be this heavy, for it is the sort of car you&#x2019;ll only pullover with at a garish party of sorts, attended by only the wealthiest of the wealthy to show off the shiny and heavy accouterments bejeweled on your ride.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Because like the Rolls Royce Phantom, the flying spur&#x2019;s luxury also rests in its weight.&nbsp; Out of the 2.4 tons, nearly one-fourth of the fitments are allocated to shiny metal bits and stuff incorporated only to give a luxury feel. It has metal all around the cabin, all buttons made out of metal, the gear handle, the cup holders, it even has an old-fashioned clock made of gold.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Volkswagen_Touareg_W12_%E2%80%93_2524_kg\"><\/span>Volkswagen Touareg W12 &#8211; 2524 kg<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"400\" height=\"200\" src=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/2005-volkswagen-touareg_100031094_m-compressed.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-814\" srcset=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/2005-volkswagen-touareg_100031094_m-compressed.jpg 400w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/2005-volkswagen-touareg_100031094_m-compressed-300x150.jpg 300w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/2005-volkswagen-touareg_100031094_m-compressed-24x12.jpg 24w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/2005-volkswagen-touareg_100031094_m-compressed-36x18.jpg 36w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/2005-volkswagen-touareg_100031094_m-compressed-48x24.jpg 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The SUVs you see today are not nearly as big as they used to be. In fact, before them, the station wagons were even more of an impractical juggernaut that phased out around the same time SUVs became popular. Today, you can choose between an SUV, a compact SUV, a crossover, and a mid-size. In the early 2000s, that wouldn&#x2019;t even mean anything as it was a different time for SUVs altogether.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>People had just left the station wagon for a much more practical alternative &#8211; an SUV. However, the early SUVs were still pretty big and the Volkswagen Touareg from 2005 being one of them was really the pinnacle of the decadence of the overweightedness of those impractical iterations.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Buick_Estate_%E2%80%93_2351_kg\"><\/span>Buick Estate &#8211; 2351 kg<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/220px-1982_Buick_Electra_Estate_in_WA_US-compressed.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-813\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" srcset=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/220px-1982_Buick_Electra_Estate_in_WA_US-compressed.jpg 220w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/220px-1982_Buick_Electra_Estate_in_WA_US-compressed-24x18.jpg 24w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/220px-1982_Buick_Electra_Estate_in_WA_US-compressed-36x27.jpg 36w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/220px-1982_Buick_Electra_Estate_in_WA_US-compressed-48x36.jpg 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 220px) 100vw, 220px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Station wagons are known to be heavier than your typical car. But one that&#x2019;s all chrome and iron, isn&#x2019;t your typical estate either. This mammoth of a car weighs in at around two tons which is a lot more than any of today&#x2019;s standard SUVs and would absolutely crush a compact SUV. The Buick estate had a long metal body that stretched, 228.3 inches in length (more than the phantom), heavily ornated interiors, and massive boot space to add more weight to the car. It was the quintessential estate to drive across the country, just not very economical though.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Audi_Q7_V12_%E2%80%93_2600_kg\"><\/span>Audi Q7 V12 &#8211; 2600 kg<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"642\" height=\"336\" src=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/Audi-Q5-Exterior-165497-compressed.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-821\" srcset=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/Audi-Q5-Exterior-165497-compressed.jpg 642w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/Audi-Q5-Exterior-165497-compressed-300x157.jpg 300w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/Audi-Q5-Exterior-165497-compressed-24x13.jpg 24w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/Audi-Q5-Exterior-165497-compressed-36x19.jpg 36w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/Audi-Q5-Exterior-165497-compressed-48x25.jpg 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 642px) 100vw, 642px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>At the time it was released, the Audi Q7 was one of the best and snippiest 0-60 SUVs out there. It didn&#x2019;t feel to be as heavy as it actually was. It in fact quickly became Audi&#x2019;s flagship SUV offering and rightly so it was the top choice for every family SUV with its quant interiors and sporty chassis. This car weighed in at 2600 kilos and was bigger than the Q8 model presently available in the market.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Audi_E-Tron_SUV_%E2%80%93_2695_kg\"><\/span>Audi E-Tron SUV &#8211; 2695 kg<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/58f62ba4f40daebe628b4a71-compressed.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-823\" width=\"428\" height=\"321\" srcset=\"https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/58f62ba4f40daebe628b4a71-compressed.jpg 856w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/58f62ba4f40daebe628b4a71-compressed-300x225.jpg 300w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/58f62ba4f40daebe628b4a71-compressed-768x576.jpg 768w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/58f62ba4f40daebe628b4a71-compressed-850x638.jpg 850w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/58f62ba4f40daebe628b4a71-compressed-24x18.jpg 24w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/58f62ba4f40daebe628b4a71-compressed-36x27.jpg 36w, https:\/\/vehiclecare.in\/blaze\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/58f62ba4f40daebe628b4a71-compressed-48x36.jpg 48w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 428px) 100vw, 428px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Whatever weight a traditional car might have, its electric version will always be certain to take it a step further. The electric variant of the Audi SUV weighs in at just under 2700 kilos which is actually rather on the low end of the weight as compared to other electric vehicles &#8211; Good job by Audi I guess. Nonetheless, it&#x2019;s still heavier than most normal SUVs.&nbsp;&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Tesla_Cybertruck_%E2%80%93_3000_kg\"><\/span>Tesla Cybertruck &#8211; 3000 kg&nbsp;<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"